docs.text: MkDocs documentation Using mkdocs for documentation. More detail about this tool at MKdocs Getting started mkdocs new my-project - Create a new project Deploy in Github Page This document will be published in Github Page. To do this, you need: Create a repository in github with name: vutang.github.io Clone this repo to local machine In local machine, use command: mkdocs gh-deploy --config-file ../mkdocs-vux-note/mkdocs.yml --remote-branch master Test with local webserver use mkdocs serve to run local web server in your browser, access http://127.0.0.1:8000 Commands mkdocs new [dir-name] - Create a new project. mkdocs serve - Start the live-reloading docs server. mkdocs build - Build the documentation site. mkdocs help - Print this help message.
